listing_jobDesc:
Flexible working hours, family friendly!
Operating Nationwide and across Indonesia!
An innovative mining haulage company known for introducing new technologies!


Bis is a mining services company who have been have been delivering logistics, materials handling, specialised equipment and consulting services to resource companies across Australia and Indonesia every day since 1915.

We are seeking a .Net Developer who will develop and deliver operational applications on a national basis for Bis.

The applications will include remote vehicle monitoring, risk, contract and form management and will involve work in various technologies including systems integration, intranet, internet, web systems and forms design (K2). The role will also develop new systems supporting ongoing innovation in Bis.

This role will be based at either the newly refurbised Osborne Park (WA) office, Sydney (NSW) or Brisbane (QLD) office.

The successful applicant will possess:
Degree qualification in Computer Science or Engineering;
Minimum 3 years’ experience in .NET application development and implementation;
Experience implementing systems as an Analyst or Key Business User;
Must have experience in building business solution using .NET, C#, ASP.NET, MVC, Web/k2 Forms, WPF, WCF, Microsoft SQL Server, JQuery, JavaScript;
Experience with IoC container - Castle Windsor, ORM – EF, Peta POCO, Microsoft SQL Server 2014, Stored Procedures, SOAP/REST Services;
Experience with CMS;
Experience in unit testing and integration testing;
Source code version control using Subversion/SVN;
Understanding of design principles and design patterns;
Understanding of software development life cycle, agile principles and iterative/incremental development;
Windows Server 2016 and IIS configuration;
An understanding of business process automation using K2 is advantageous but not essential;
Ability to understand complex business requirements and architecture and build solution;
Ability to write reports, business correspondence and procedure manuals;
Ability to effectively present information and respond to questions from groups of managers, users and customers;
Ability to meet deadlines and prioritise multiple tasks.
Advantageous:
Experience with Azure Dev Ops is essential
(Git /Bit Bucket)
An understanding of business process automation using K2 is advantageous but not essential
Websockets or Real-time Application Development
We are your resources logistics company
We find the best solutions and inventive ways to improve while looking after the health, safety and well-being of our people, the communities we operate in and our environment. Our strong team focus enables us to solve problems for our customers while also providing a unique culture that is built on the valued contribution our people make, every day. Flexible working hours, family friendly!
